article_title: Officials Look Into Cause Of Fire At SE OKC Warehouse - News9.com - Oklahoma City, OK - News, Weather, Video and Sports
article_text:
According to the fire department, crews responded to the fire just before 6 a.m. at a structure in the 2300 block of S.E. 15th Street.

Firefighters contained a fire at a southeast Oklahoma City warehouse Tuesday morning.

According to the fire department, crews responded to the fire just before 6 a.m. at a structure in the 2300 block of S.E. 15th Street. They were able to contain the fire.

Crews also say some beams inside the commercial building (that stores oil field equipment) are bent from fire. Not going in just yet. @NEWS9 — Justin Dougherty (@DoughertyNews9) December 22, 2015

The cause of the fire is under investigation.
